The '''Final Redoubt''' was supposedly the name of a secret [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] base on the moon of [[Ebaq 9]] during the latter half of the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]]. Elements of [[Chief of State (New Republic)/Legends|Chief of State]] [[Cal Omas]]' staff, a large contingent of [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] and much of the waning New Republic's strategic resources were rumored to be hidden there.

Unbeknownst, however, to the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] and [[Peace Brigade]] spies to whom this information was leaked, no such base existed. Meticulous planning on behalf of the [[New Republic Intelligence Service]] had uncovered the Yuuzhan Vong spy network on [[Mon Calamari/Legends|Mon Calamari]] and fed it false information, hoping that the Yuuzhan Vong would reach the conclusion that this last bastion of the New Republic could be caught unaware and destroyed. In this they were successful; [[Supreme Overlord]] [[Shimrra Jamaane]], persuaded by his [[Executor (Yuuzhan Vong rank)|executor]] [[Nom Anor]], ordered [[Warmaster]] [[Tsavong Lah]] to take a task force and wipe out the base.[[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Gial Ackbar/Legends|Ackbar's]] resulting trap led to the [[Battle of Ebaq]] 9, the devastation of Lah's task force and the death of the warmaster himself.

